    "The GANs are unsupervised generative models that automatically locate the data distribution [3].",
    "The \"Generator\" and the \"Discriminator\" are the two main models in a GAN system.",
    "One type of neural network, a convolutional network, is responsible for generating data, while another type of network, a deconvolution network, is used for classification.",
    "Conceptually, GAN uses a supervised learning approach to generate synthetic data, allowing it to engage in unsupervised learning.",
    "The model assumes the structures present in data sets without taking into consideration findings that have been anticipated, labelled, or classified [4]."
